1
00:00:00,335 --> 00:00:04,859
♪A little bit sorry for my love for you♪

2
00:00:04,859 --> 00:00:10,363
♪Sorry, I was a little late♪

3
00:00:10,363 --> 00:00:16,791
♪I really want the unconscious longing
to appear faster♪

4
00:00:16,791 --> 00:00:21,271
♪Can I get closer
and hear you say "I do" once more♪

5
00:00:21,271 --> 00:00:25,719
♪Holding hands, the scenery
in midsummer is a new journey♪

6
00:00:25,719 --> 00:00:30,630
♪The chapters of a fairy tale
are performed one after another♪

7
00:00:30,630 --> 00:00:34,679
♪The promised moment
will definitely not be forgotten♪

8
00:00:34,679 --> 00:00:39,214
♪Can I get closer and listen to
the frequency of your heartbeat♪

9
00:00:39,214 --> 00:00:43,511
♪Start the countdown 4321,
a new scenery♪

10
00:00:43,511 --> 00:00:48,276
♪I want to see all the scenes about you♪

11
00:00:48,276 --> 00:00:51,767
♪No need to miss you anymore♪

12
00:00:51,767 --> 00:00:55,447
♪Right by your side♪

13
00:00:57,093 --> 00:01:00,471
=Jin Secretary=

14
00:01:00,471 --> 00:01:03,159
=Episode 25=

15
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:09,033
Lan Chen.

16
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:24,500
Is he okay?

17
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:26,266
He got drunk. I'll take him home.

18
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,233
I can take him home.

19
00:01:28,766 --> 00:01:30,366
No need. I'll call a taxi.

20
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:31,966
I'll take him home.

21
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:34,633
Then let's go together.

22
00:01:36,366 --> 00:01:39,766
Okay, wait a moment.
I'll call the driver now.

23
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:40,672
Okay.

24
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,266
Slow down.

25
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,333
What happened to Mr. Lan?

26
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:50,366
He's drunk.

27
00:01:50,366 --> 00:01:52,166
Where is his room? We'll take him up.

28
00:01:52,166 --> 00:01:53,666
Please follow me.

29
00:02:00,533 --> 00:02:02,533
Be careful.

30
00:02:18,112 --> 00:02:19,300
Mr. Zeng, let's go.

31
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:20,233
Okay.

32
00:02:20,233 --> 00:02:21,566
Don't leave, Miss Jin.

33
00:02:28,633 --> 00:02:29,933
He's really drunk.

34
00:02:30,633 --> 00:02:31,833
Don't leave.

35
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:38,333
I don't know what's wrong with him.

36
00:02:41,133 --> 00:02:43,566
It's late. I'll take you home.

37
00:02:43,566 --> 00:02:45,633
Okay. By the way,

38
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:47,133
get him something for his hangover.

39
00:02:47,166 --> 00:02:48,400
Okay.

40
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:56,640
Are you alright?

41
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:04,633
It is hot. You got caught in the rain?

42
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:08,000
It's okay. I'm indestructible.

43
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,600
Fine.

44
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:14,720
Hey.

45
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:19,133
Please bring me some medicine for fever
and a warm towel?

46
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,200
I'll go get them now.

47
00:03:21,433 --> 00:03:23,666
Why don't you take her
to the guest room downstairs first?

48
00:03:23,666 --> 00:03:25,472
Okay.

49
00:03:51,366 --> 00:03:52,800
Don't worry, Heroine.

50
00:03:53,966 --> 00:03:56,866
You just rest well.
Leave the rest to me.

51
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,366
You've taken care of too many people.

52
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,766
Let me take care of you now.

53
00:04:06,133 --> 00:04:07,166
Thank you, Mr. Zeng.

54
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,536
Good night.

55
00:04:22,366 --> 00:04:24,166
I'm going to make a sandwich today.

56
00:04:25,566 --> 00:04:29,333
Miss Jin was sick last night.
She needs to eat something light.

57
00:04:30,633 --> 00:04:32,833
Sure, I'm making a salad.

58
00:04:36,966 --> 00:04:39,533
It seems that you often cook.

59
00:04:40,766 --> 00:04:42,266
I only cook for the people I love.

60
00:04:44,233 --> 00:04:45,200
Who doesn't?

61
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:02,733
(Lan Chen's clothes)

62
00:05:04,233 --> 00:05:06,766
Miss Jin, are you feeling better?

63
00:05:06,766 --> 00:05:08,500
Yeah.

64
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:11,800
You had a fever last night.
Mr. Zeng and Mr. Lan took turns

65
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,633
at looking after you.

66
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:15,633
He didn't leave?

67
00:05:15,633 --> 00:05:17,333
Yes, he just left.

68
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:20,566
Where are they now?

69
00:05:20,766 --> 00:05:21,966
They are in the kitchen.

70
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:24,400
Okay, thank you.

71
00:05:25,133 --> 00:05:26,784
You're welcome.

72
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:32,633
Is yours ready yet?

73
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:36,266
You tell me if it's too salty.

74
00:05:38,528 --> 00:05:39,800
How is it?

75
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,184
It's fine.

76
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,266
You try my salad.

77
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,633
Is the taste okay? I put a little salt.

78
00:05:52,100 --> 00:05:53,536
Is it salty?

79
00:05:55,533 --> 00:05:56,633
It's too salty.

80
00:05:57,566 --> 00:05:59,400
Impossible. How could it be salty?

81
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,000
Miss Jin can't eat something that salty.

82
00:06:02,266 --> 00:06:03,648
It's not salty.

83
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,333
What are you two doing?

84
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:28,066
Are you feeling better, Heroine?

85
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:36,566
Why didn't you wear my clothes?
What if you catch a cold later?

86
00:06:37,966 --> 00:06:39,633
I'm wearing enough.

87
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,833
Come.

88
00:06:46,100 --> 00:06:47,584
Thank you.

89
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:55,968
Here.

90
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,566
Thank you both.

91
00:07:01,233 --> 00:07:02,816
Go ahead.

92
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:05,833
Try this.

93
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:12,133
This is really good.

94
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,133
Do you like it?

95
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:16,333
I'll make it for you every day.

96
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:17,408
Humph.

97
00:07:19,633 --> 00:07:20,600
I have to go.

98
00:07:20,633 --> 00:07:21,666
I have work to do.

99
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:25,033
Right. I'm giving you the day off today.

100
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:27,366
See you tomorrow.

101
00:07:27,366 --> 00:07:30,233
Miss Jin, we can hang out today.

102
00:07:30,233 --> 00:07:31,680
Okay.

103
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,666
Mr. Lan, you do your things.

104
00:07:40,233 --> 00:07:41,600
Eat up.

105
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,666
See you. And this is for you.

106
00:07:51,133 --> 00:07:52,233
What happened?

107
00:08:07,366 --> 00:08:08,864
Miss Jin?

108
00:08:10,233 --> 00:08:15,200
Boss, this is our schedule and plan,

109
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:17,966
and suggestions for the design draft.

110
00:08:20,966 --> 00:08:22,566
Didn't I give you a day off?

111
00:08:23,133 --> 00:08:27,066
Can you fly?
How did you get here so quickly?

112
00:08:27,866 --> 00:08:28,733
I fly?

113
00:08:33,071 --> 00:08:37,593
♪I pass through the crowd with you♪

114
00:08:40,623 --> 00:08:45,584
♪As if we have a tacit understanding,
attracting each other♪

115
00:08:48,633 --> 00:08:54,457
♪When the loneliness cracks,
warmth seeps in♪

116
00:08:54,457 --> 00:09:01,927
♪You come with light,
shining into my heart♪

117
00:09:01,927 --> 00:09:05,408
♪Stars fall into my eyes,
and you fall into my heart♪

118
00:09:05,408 --> 00:09:09,529
♪I make a wish foolishly,
but actually, you are the shooting star♪

119
00:09:09,529 --> 00:09:11,225
♪Open my secret♪

120
00:09:11,225 --> 00:09:17,273
♪I hope you find
all the tenderness hidden for you♪

121
00:09:17,273 --> 00:09:21,145
♪Sinking into your love,
I want to sink deeper♪

122
00:09:21,145 --> 00:09:25,651
♪With each breath,
I can feel the sweetness♪

123
00:09:25,651 --> 00:09:34,361
♪Two lonely islands meet,
and it's the gift of fate♪
